               <provenance>According to the colophon, the Ms. was
                     commissioned by priest (qes gabaz) ʾabuna
                     Takla Hāymānot and donated to the church of Yoḥannǝs Maṭmǝq of Dǝbla. The name
                     of the donor and the names of his family members are written in the
                     supplication formulas throughout the Ms.: Takla Hāymānot (e.g., 6vb, 13vb, 16ra, 21ra, 26va, 27vb, 28rb, 29rb, 52rb),
                     his father Walda Mikāʾel (6vb, 13vb, 16ra, 26va,
                     28ra, 29ra, 52rb), Walatta Kidān (23vb, 27va) and
                     Ṣädalä Māryām (29rb, 32rb).</provenance></history>
